---
import { BaseLayout } from "@walle/layouts";
---

<BaseLayout
  headerTitle="Privacy Policy"
  headerDescription="Read our privacy policy to learn how we handle your data."
  headerRobots="noindex, nofollow"
>
  <main class="container prose">
    <h1 style="padding-top: 2rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: Jul 22, 2025</p>
    <p>
      This notice describes how Fabrizio Cafolla (<a
        href="https://fabriziocafolla.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">fabriziocafolla.com</a
      >) collects and processes usersâ€™ personal data through the use of Piwik PRO, exclusively for
      anonymous and aggregated statistical analysis purposes.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Data Controller</h4>
    <p>
      The data controller is Fabrizio Cafolla, owner of this blog. For any privacy-related requests,
      you can contact me via LinkedIn.
    </p>

    <h4>2. Data Collected</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Personal data:</strong> No personal data is collected from users visiting the site.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Anonymous statistical data:</strong> Only anonymous and aggregated data is collected
        for statistical analysis, in order to improve content and browsing experience. This data does
        not allow direct or indirect identification of site visitors.
      </li>
      <li>
        Piwik PRO may collect the following information: Operating system and browser type, Country,
        Browsing activity (pages visited, session duration, referrer), technical and analytics
        cookies.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Purpose and Legal Basis of Processing</h4>
    <h5>3.1 Analytics</h5>
    <p>
      Processing is based on the user's consent, pursuant to Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR. Upon first access to
      the site, consent is requested via a banner; if consent is not given, data is not collected.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Statistical analysis on site usage</li>
      <li>Improvement of the services offered</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>3.2 Newsletter</h5>
    <p>
      Processing of newsletter subscription data is based on your explicit consent pursuant to Art.
      6(1)(a) GDPR and Art. 130 of Italian Legislative Decree 196/2003 (Privacy Code).
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sending newsletter communications about new articles published on the blog</li>
      <li>Managing subscription and unsubscription requests</li>
      <li>Compliance with legal obligations related to electronic communications</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>4. Cookies</h4>
    <p>
      The site may use technical and/or anonymous analytics cookies (e.g., cookies for aggregated
      and anonymous statistical analysis). No profiling or marketing cookies are used.
    </p>

    <h4>5. Data Processing and Third Parties</h4>

    <h5>5.1 Analytics - Piwik PRO</h5>
    <p>
      The collected analytics data is not shared with third parties. It is not transmitted to
      sub-processors or third parties and is not used by Piwik PRO for its own purposes. Data is
      retained for a maximum of 14 months.
    </p>

    <h5>5.2 Newsletter - Brevo</h5>
    <p>
      Newsletter subscription data is processed through Brevo (formerly Sendinblue), a marketing
      automation platform. By subscribing to the newsletter, you agree that your personal
      information will be transferred to Brevo for processing in accordance with <a
        href="https://www.brevo.com/legal/privacypolicy/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">Brevo's Privacy Policy</a
      >. Brevo acts as a data processor and processes data exclusively on our behalf and according
      to our instructions. Data transfer to Brevo is based on adequate safeguards as required by
      GDPR.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Users' Rights</h4>

    <h5>6.1 Analytics</h5>
    <p>
      Since no personal data is collected for analytics, it is not possible to identify users or
      exercise rights related to personal data (such as access, rectification, or deletion). Consent
      can be withdrawn at any time via browser settings or the cookie banner.
    </p>

    <h5>6.2 Newsletter</h5>
    <p>
      Regarding newsletter subscription data, you can unsubscribe at any time using the link in
      emails or contacting us directly.
    </p>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact me using the contact details available on the site. You also
      have the right to lodge a complaint with the Italian Data Protection Authority (Garante per la
      protezione dei dati personali).
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
